'''多鄰國'''（{{lang-en|Duolingo}}；{{IPAc-en|ˌ|dj|uː|oʊ|ˈ|l|ɪ|ŋ|ɡ|oʊ}} {{respell|DEW|oh|LING|goh}}）是[[美國|美國]]一個[[語言習得|語言學習]]網站及應用程式。該公司以[[免費增值|免費增值]]模式營運：網站及應用程式皆免費使用，但也有提供付費升級版本。

截至2021年6月，多鄰國提供了40種語言共106種的語言課程，也有許多語言課程正在開發中。<ref name="bizjournals201603">{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/news/2016/03/23/duolingo-moving-to-east-liberty-plans-to-add.html |publisher=The Business Journals |title=Duolingo moving to East Liberty, plans to add employees |accessdate=2016-03-24 |archive-date=2017-05-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170531182842/http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/news/2016/03/23/duolingo-moving-to-east-liberty-plans-to-add.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | publisher = Microsoft | work = Windows phone | url = http://www.windowsphone.com/en-us/store/app/duolingo-learn-languages-for-free/2d89520e-d360-4b5b-ba5a-5a15064aa935 | title = Duolingo – Learn Languages for Free | accessdate = 2014-11-21 | archive-date = 2015-07-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150702044316/http://www.windowsphone.com/en-us/store/app/duolingo-learn-languages-for-free/2d89520e-d360-4b5b-ba5a-5a15064aa935 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/parulguliani/2016/07/22/duolingo-looks-to-dominate-the-mobile-education-market-with-new-flashcard-app/#5530e29a63ff|title=Duolingo Looks To Dominate The Mobile Education Market With New Flashcard App TinyCards|last=Guliani|first=Parul|newspaper=Forbes|access-date=2017-02-17|archive-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130074739/https://www.forbes.com/sites/parulguliani/2016/07/22/duolingo-looks-to-dominate-the-mobile-education-market-with-new-flashcard-app/#5530e29a63ff|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://expandedramblings.com/index.php/business-directory/24390/duolingo-stats-facts/|title=By the Numbers: 16 Amazing Duolingo Stats and Facts (October 2017)|newspaper=DMR|accessdate=2017-11-06|language=en-US|archive-date=2017-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107024446/https://expandedramblings.com/index.php/business-directory/24390/duolingo-stats-facts/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==歷史==
多鄰國起源於2009年，[[美国|美国]][[匹兹堡|匹兹堡]][[卡内基梅隆大学|卡内基梅隆大学]]的[[路易斯·馮·安|路易斯·馮·安]]教授（[[reCAPTCHA|reCAPTCHA计划]]的发起人）和他的研究生Severin Hacker发起<ref name="TechCrunch Article" /><ref name="Duolingo Team" />，并主要是以[[Python|Python]]写成<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.quora.com/What-language-is-多邻国-written-in |title=What language is 多邻国 written in? |publisher=Quora |date= |accessdate=2014-02-21}}</ref>。多鄰國（Duolingo）的名字來自[[拉丁语|拉丁文]]字根，''duo''(兩個)和''lingo''(語言)；易斯·馮·安授希望多鄰國使用者一方面在學習一種語言時，也能反身過來協助建構多鄰國的語言課程，讓其他人也能多學習一種語言<ref>{{Cite book|title = Learning with Big Data: The Future of Education|last1 = Mayer-Schönberger|first1 = Viktor|publisher = Houghton Mifflin Harcourt |year = 2014|isbn = 978-0-54435550-7|location = |pages = 9–10|url = https://books.google.com/?id=OXzeAgAAQBAJ&pg=PP1 |last2 = Cukier |first2 = Kenneth}}</ref>；這種模式稱為[[众包|众包]]，它的设计理念是，当用户逐渐学习课程时，同时也在帮助翻译网站上的内容或文件<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.technologyreview.com/computing/37487/ |publisher=Technology Review|title=Translating the Web While You Learn}}</ref><ref name="TechCrunch Article" />。

多鄰國早期由路易斯·馮·安教授所获的[[麦克阿瑟奖|麦克阿瑟奖金]]和[[国家科学基金会|美国国家科学基金会]]赞助<ref name="NSFGrant" /><ref name="NewScientist" />，随后的资金来自Union Square Ventures公司以及演员[[艾希顿·库奇|Ashton Kutcher]]的A-Grade Investments公司的投资<ref name="pittsgazzette" />。

多邻国在2011年11月30日发布了[[软件测试#封测与公测|封测版本]]，其試用者候補名單甚至累積到超过300,000用户<ref name="DuoBlog">{{cite web |url=http://blog.duolingo.com/post/20142464554/we-have-a-blog |publisher=Duolingo Blog |title=We have a blog! |access-date=2014-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120401200917/http://blog.duolingo.com/post/20142464554/we-have-a-blog |archive-date=2012-04-01 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theverge.com/2011/12/16/2639262/duolingo-translate-internet-teach-languages|title=Duolingo will translate the internet while teaching languages|author=Adi Robertson|publisher=''[[The_Verge|The Verge]]''|date=December 16, 2011|accessdate=February 3, 2016|archive-date=2020-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201013182550/https://www.theverge.com/2011/12/16/2639262/duolingo-translate-internet-teach-languages|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2012年6月19日，多鄰國向公众开放。2012年11月23日，多邻国在苹果[[App_Store_(iOS)|App Store]]发布了[[iOS|iOS]]应用<ref>{{cite web |title=Duolingo on the go. Our iPhone App is here! |url=http://blog.duolingo.com/post/35638702323/Duolingo-on-the-go-our-iphone-app-is-here |publisher=Duolingo |date=2012-11-13 |accessdate=2012-11-27 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212062452/http://blog.duolingo.com/post/35638702323/duolingo-on-the-go-our-iphone-app-is-here |archive-date=2013-12-12 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="TCiOS">{{cite web|url=http://techcrunch.com/2012/11/13/language-learning-service-duolingo-launches-its-first-iphone-app/|title=Language Learning Service Duolingo Launches Its First iPhone App|author=Frederic Lardinois|work=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]]|publisher=[[AOL|AOL]]|date=2012-11-13|accessdate=2016-04-18|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116185624/https://techcrunch.com/2012/11/13/language-learning-service-duolingo-launches-its-first-iphone-app/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这款应用程式提供免费下载，并兼容大部分[[iPhone|iPhone]]、[[iPod_touch|iPod touch]]和[[iPad|iPad]]设备<ref>{{cite web|title=Duolingo – Learn Spanish, French, German, Portuguese, and Italian for free|url=https://itunes.apple.com/app/duolingo-learn-spanish-french/id570060128|work=iTunes App Store|publisher=Apple|accessdate=2013-04-29|archive-date=2019-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190506091422/https://itunes.apple.com/app/duolingo-learn-spanish-french/id570060128|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2013年，多邻国被苹果选为iPhone年度APP，这也是教育類App首次獲得此一榮譽<ref name="gigaom" />。

2013年5月29日，多邻国发布了[[Android|安卓]]app，发布前三周就被下载超过一百万次，很快成为[[Google_Play|Google Play商店]]下载量第一的教育类app<ref>{{cite web |last=Farber |first=Dan |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-1023_3-57593078-93/Duolingo-brings-free-language-courses-to-the-ipad/ |title=Duolingo brings free language courses to the iPad |publisher=News.cnet.com |date=2013-07-11 |accessdate=2014-02-21 |archive-date=2019-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190421184610/https://www.cnet.com/news/duolingo-brings-free-language-courses-to-the-ipad/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。{{as of|2013|5}}，多邻国有27名雇员，办公地点位于[[匹兹堡|匹兹堡]]旁边的Shadyside，并且在[[卡内基梅隆大学|卡内基梅隆大学]]旁。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/blog/innovation/2013/05/Duolingo-launching-on-android-signing.html?page=all |title=Duolingo launching on Android; plans move to bigger office |publisher=Bizjournals.com |date=2013-05-29 |accessdate=2014-02-21 |archive-date=2020-08-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200811165651/https://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/blog/innovation/2013/05/Duolingo-launching-on-android-signing.html?page=all |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2021年7月28日，多邻国在纳斯达克挂牌上市，股票代码为“DUOL”。

==商业模式==
多邻国平台的核心服務都是免費的。對手機用戶端來說，使用者只會在完成一個單元的學習後才會看到一次廣告，相比整個使用時間來說相當有限。使用多鄰國平台的學生無需支付服務費。然而，多鄰國也有少數需要收費的應用程式內購買服務。

2014年7月，多鄰國開設了語言認證服務。

===众包翻译===
多鄰國最初採取[[众包|众包]]的模式盈利：在这种模式中，会员们会被邀请来参与文本翻译和给翻译投票。这些文本来自一些组织，多邻国为他们翻译文本来获得收益。要翻译的文本会通过一个申请过的上传账号添加到多邻国上<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.technologyreview.com/news/506656/the-cleverest-business-model-in-online-education/ |last=Simonite |first=Tom |title=The Cleverest Business Model in Online Education |publisher=Technologyreview.com |date=2012-11-29 |accessdate=2014-02-21 |language=en |archive-date=2015-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151127160721/http://www.technologyreview.com/news/506656/the-cleverest-business-model-in-online-education/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2013年10月14日， 多邻国宣布与[[CNN|CNN]]和[[BuzzFeed|BuzzFeed]]达成协议，为这两家公司的国际网页翻译文章<ref>{{cite web |title=Duolingo now translating BuzzFeed and CNN |url=http://blog.duolingo.com/post/64024962586/Duolingo-now-translating-buzzfeed-and-cnn |publisher=Duolingo |date=2013-10-14 |accessdate=2013-11-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140209111042/http://blog.duolingo.com/post/64024962586/duolingo-now-translating-buzzfeed-and-cnn |archive-date=2014-02-09 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=BuzzFeed Expands Internationally In Partnership With Duolingo |url=http://www.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeedpress/buzzfeed-expands-internationally-in-partnership-with-duoling |publisher=Buzz Feed |date=2013-10-14 |accessdate=2013-11-07 |language=en |archive-date=2020-11-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124050307/https://www.buzzfeed.com/buzzfeedpress/buzzfeed-expands-internationally-in-partnership-with-duoling |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==语言孵化器==
语言孵化器<ref>{{cite web | url = https://incubator.duolingo.com/ | title = Incubator | publisher = Duolingo | access-date = 2017-02-22 | archive-date = 2021-01-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210122064243/https://www.duolingo.com/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>，发布於2013年10月9日<ref>{{cite news |last= Olson |first= Parmy |title= Duolingo Takes Online Teaching To The Next Level, by Crowd Sourcing New Languages |url= http://www.forbes.com/sites/parmyolson/2013/09/25/duolingo-takes-online-teaching-to-next-level-by-crowd-sourcing-new-languages/ |work= Forbes |accessdate= 2014-04-07 |archive-date= 2020-11-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201111205855/https://www.forbes.com/sites/parmyolson/2013/09/25/duolingo-takes-online-teaching-to-next-level-by-crowd-sourcing-new-languages/ |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.duolingo.com/comment/930039| title=Discussion| publisher=Duolingo| accessdate=2013-10-09| archive-date=2017-11-07| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107055908/https://www.duolingo.com/comment/930039| dead-url=no}}</ref>，是使用者貢獻自身語言知識，協助建立多鄰國課程的服務。

除了帮助学习社区为多数语言（被广泛使用的语言）开发课程，多邻国孵化器也旨在保存一些少数语言，例如[[拉丁语|拉丁语]]、[[玛雅语系|玛雅语系]]和[[巴斯克语|巴斯克语]]<ref name=cnn-incibator>{{cite news |url= http://edition.cnn.com/2013/10/15/tech/mobile/duolingo-incubator-language-teaching/ |title= Duolingo 'incubator' aims to crowdsource language teaching |publisher= [[CNN|CNN]] |date= 2013-10-15 |accessdate= 2014-02-21 |archive-date= 2021-02-16 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210216212021/https://edition.cnn.com/2013/10/15/tech/mobile/duolingo-incubator-language-teaching/ |dead-url= no }}</ref>。

多邻国社区第一个完全通过孵化器开发的课程，是基于俄语学习英语，2013年12月19日发布了此课程的[[软件版本周期#Beta|beta]]版本<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.duolingo.com/comment/1305305 |title= English from Russian is now available in beta! |publisher= Duolingo |accessdate= 2014-02-21 |archive-date= 2016-05-29 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160529013947/https://www.duolingo.com/comment/1305305 |dead-url= no }}</ref>。多邻国社区开发的其他课程，包括基于土耳其语、荷兰语、匈牙利语学习英语 ，以及基于西班牙语学习法语、葡萄牙语。

孵化器有三个阶段。首先，如果双方面语言都很流利的志愿者们有足够的兴趣来开发项目（这是申请前提），那么一门语言课程就可以开始“阶段一：尚未发布”。当课程准备已充分并且可以用于版本测试时，就可以进入“阶段二：Beta版本发布.最后，一旦所有课程内容达到能够向公众发布的阶段时，就进入“阶段三：向公众发布”。如果已完成的课程依然待在孵化器中，那是因为负责人在继续做微调以改进课程。例如，一个学生答错问题，并且发现系统出现问题，它会误导学生或会把正确答案判错，那么这名学生就可以提交报告来阐述系统问题。

